      "title": "Optical property of parabola ",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>The optical property of a parabola</strong></h3><p>The tangent at any point $\\text{P}$ on a parabola bisects the angle between the focal chord</p><p>through $\\text{P}$ and the perpendicular from $\\text{P}$ on the directrx.</p><p><strong>Sol. </strong>Let the parabola be</p><p>${{\\text{y}}^{2}}=4\\text{ax}$</p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=\"242\" height=\"181\">&nbsp;</p><p>Let $\\text{P}\\left( \\text{a}{{\\text{t}}^{2}},2\\text{at} \\right)$ at a point on parabola (1) and let PM $\\bot $ the directrix.</p><p>Equation of the tangent to parabola (1) at $\\text{P}$ is</p><p>$\\text{yt}=\\text{x}+\\text{at}{{\\text{t}}^{2}}$</p><p>Slope of this tangent PT, $\\text{tan}\\theta =\\frac{1}{\\text{t}}$</p><p>$\\begin{array}{l} {} &amp; \\text{ Slope }~\\text{ of }~PS=\\frac{2at}{a\\left( {{t}^{2}}-1 \\right)}=\\frac{2t}{{{t}^{2}}-1}=\\frac{\\frac{2}{t}}{1-\\frac{1}{{{t}^{2}}}} \\\\ {} &amp; ~=\\frac{2\\text{tan}\\theta }{1-\\text{ta}{{\\text{n}}^{2}}\\theta }=\\text{tan}2\\theta \\\\ {} &amp; \\begin{align} &amp; ~\\therefore \\angle \\text{PSX}=2\\theta \\\\ &amp; \\therefore \\angle TPS=\\angle PSX-\\angle PTS=20-\\theta =\\theta \\\\ \\end{align} \\\\ {} &amp; \\text{ Hence }~\\angle \\text{SPT}=\\angle \\text{MPT}=\\theta \\\\ \\end{array}$</p><p>Therefore PT bisects $\\angle $ MPS.</p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=\"250\" height=\"193\">&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Note. Reflection from the parabola of a ray parallel to the axis :&nbsp;</strong></p><p>In $\\text{ }\\!\\!\\Delta\\!\\!\\text{ }$ PTN</p><p>$\\angle \\text{TPN}=90$ and $\\angle \\text{PTN}=\\theta $</p><p>Since PR | | TN</p><p>$\\therefore \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }\\angle \\text{RPN}=\\angle \\text{TNP}=90-\\theta $</p><p>[. $\\angle \\text{TNP}=90-\\theta $ ]</p><p>Also $\\begin{array}{*{35}{l}} \\angle \\text{SPN} &amp; ~=180-\\angle \\text{PSN}-\\angle \\text{SNP} \\\\ {} &amp; ~=180-2\\theta -\\left( 90-\\theta \\right) \\\\ {} &amp; ~=90-\\theta \\\\ \\end{array}$</p><p>$\\therefore $ $\\angle \\text{SPN}=\\angle \\text{RPN}$</p><p>Hence A ray parallel to the axis of the parabola after reflection from the parabola</p><p>passes through the focus.</p>",
      "position": 0,
      "qcConcept": "66a0dd9fc03b9dcaf1afebed"
    }
